law.text:
The legislative body of a participating governmental unit may withdraw from participation in a State system and transfer to a local pension system or another State system any of the following groups of employees of the governmental unit who consent to the withdrawal, and who qualify for membership in the State system or local pension system:
all employees of the participating governmental unit;
fire fighters;
law enforcement personnel;
detention center officers; or
subject to the approval of the Board of Trustees, a homogeneous unit of at least 10 employees.
